Final Project — End-to-End Regression Pipeline:
Pick a real dataset from Kaggle (e.g. House Prices, Car Price Prediction, or Medical Insurance
Cost). Build a complete regression pipeline from raw file to evaluated model: load and inspect
→ EDA with key plots → clean all issues → preprocess all features → split into train/test → train
Simple Linear, Multiple Linear, Polynomial, Ridge, and Lasso Regression models → evaluate
each using MAE, RMSE, and R² → compare all models in a final summary table → save the
best model using pickle and reload it to predict on 5 new unseen samples. Write a short
README.txt summarising the dataset, key findings from EDA, every preprocessing decision
made, and which model performed best and why
